modules.description: Converts between lambda streams and Lwt promises or streams, extracting first or last values, transforming entire streams into lists, and enabling interoperability between asynchronous data flows. Operates on finite asynchronous streams and Lwt-based asynchronous values. Enables integration of lambda stream processing with Lwt-based asynchronous workflows, such as handling event-driven data sources or coordinating multiple asynchronous computations.

Processes lazy sequences using lambda expressions, enabling transformation and composition of data streams. Operates on lazy lists and thunks, supporting deferred evaluation and incremental processing. Enables efficient handling of large datasets and real-time data pipelines.

Converts between lambda streams and Lwt promises or streams, supporting extraction of first or last values, stream-to-list transformation, and seamless integration of asynchronous data flows. Processes finite asynchronous streams and Lwt-based values, enabling coordination of event-driven data sources and parallel computations. Allows transformation of stream sequences into concrete data structures for further processing. Example uses include fetching and aggregating data from multiple asynchronous endpoints or handling real-time event streams.
